    <section class="page-section" style="margin-top: 20px;">   
        <div class="container">    
            <div class="section-title">
			 Professional Group D (Ages 16-18) - First Prize
			  <span class="icon-red"></span>
			  <div class="section-line"></div>
			</div>
            <div class="row" style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">              
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>A Horse's Monologue</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
						Artwork Title: <b>A Horse's Monologue</b><br/>
						Artist: <b>Rachel Gu</b><br/>  
						Group D First Prize<br/>
						Group D: Ages 16-18<br/>
						Meihui Art Studio
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Artwork Description</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
A brown horse gazes outward through the canvas. Its clear eyes seem to hold many unspoken words. The gray-green background makes its coat appear luminous, while delicate brushwork gives the horse a gentle temperament. Those unspoken words may express joy at becoming the zodiac symbol of 2026, or perhaps a wish to tell its own story.
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Comments</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
This work is a close-up portrait of a horse. Against a pale green background, a dark brown horse looks forward thoughtfully, calm and peaceful, with determination and hope in its eyes.<br>
A close-up head portrait requires strong technique, especially in expressing the eyes. This work succeeds in that regard. The mane is realistic and layered, and the strong light-dark contrast gives the painting a vivid three-dimensional quality. The work feels alive and energetic, showing a solid foundation in Western painting.<br>
There is nothing excessive in the picture. Precision and expressive restraint define the essential tone of the work.
                    </div>           
                </div>  
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">                  
                    <img style="max-width: 90%" src="2026paint/D1.jpeg" /> 
                </div>                             
            </div>                 
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="page-section" style="margin-top: 20px;">   
        <div class="container">    
            <div class="section-title">
			 Professional Group C (Ages 13-15) - First Prize
			  <span class="icon-red"></span>
			  <div class="section-line"></div>
			</div>
            <div class="row" style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">              
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>Two Steeds Welcome Spring and Great Ambitions</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
						Artwork Title: <b>Two Steeds Welcome Spring and Great Ambitions</b><br/>
						Artist: <b>Victoria Tsao</b><br/>  
						Group C First Prize<br/>
						Group C: Ages 13-15 <br/>           
						Jade's Art Studio 
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Artwork Description</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
A chestnut steed and a black horse rear toward one another, manes flying, ready to gallop together across the spring earth under the rising sun and pursue great ambitions.
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Comments</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
1. The work closely follows the theme. The two horses lift their heads and hooves, showing strength and an uplifting spirit while also suggesting the auspicious meaning of success and striving forward.<br>
2. The artist handles the horses' muscular structure and dynamic posture well. The deep texture of the black horse and the glossy layers of the brown horse are clearly distinguished. The softness of the grass and the hazy distant mountains create spatial depth and the open, poetic feeling of a morning wilderness.<br>
3. The composition moves beyond the common image of a single galloping horse or a herd in motion. By using two horses facing each other, it creates visual balance and strong tension, giving the scene dramatic force.<br>
4. The open field and gradual sky leave room for imagination: are these two horses meeting for the first time in the sunrise, or standing together in pursuit of freedom? This restrained storytelling makes the work more affecting.
                    </div>           
                </div>  
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">                  
                    <img style="max-width: 90%" src="2026paint/C1.jpeg" /> 
                </div>                             
            </div>                 
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="page-section" style="margin-top: 20px;">   
        <div class="container">    
            <div class="section-title">
			Professional Group B (Ages 8-12) - First Prize
			  <span class="icon-red"></span>
			  <div class="section-line"></div>
			</div>
            <div class="row" style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">              
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>White Colt Among Peonies</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
						Artwork Title: <b>White Colt Among Peonies</b><br/>
						Artist: <b>Stella Yuanliu</b><br/>  
						Group B First Prize<br/>
						Group B: Ages 8-12 <br/>           
						Talent Color Art School  
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Artwork Description</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
Yellow peonies, with their central color, symbolize kindness and harmony;<br>
the white horse, upright in nature, represents guardianship and distant journeys.<br>
Flowers nurture the heart; the horse carries the way. Gentleness becomes virtue, and uprightness becomes action.
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Comments</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
The combination of 3D and 2D elements creates a distinctive composition. The use of contrasting blue and yellow is balanced, warm, and pleasing.<br>
Even with many yellow flowers, the horse's head remains the focal point.<br>
The artist shows skilled technique and fluent brushwork.<br>
The composition uniquely combines 3D and 2D elements. The use of contrasting blue and yellow colours creates a harmonious, warm, and comfortable effect.<br>
Even the abundance of yellow flowers doesn't overshadow the focal point—the horse's head.<br>
The artist's technique is skillful, with fluid brushstrokes.
                    </div>           
                </div>  
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">                  
                    <img style="max-width: 90%" src="2026paint/B1.jpeg" /> 
                </div>                             
            </div>                 
        </div>
    </section>
    
