            <div class="row" style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">              
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>Totem and Bronze Horse</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
						Artwork Title: <b>Totem and Bronze Horse</b><br/>
						Artist: <b>Chris Wang</b><br/>  
						Group A First Prize<br/>
						Group A: Ages 4-7 <br/>           
						Tian Tian Art Class  
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Artwork Description</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
This work stages an encounter between two ancient cultures. With an Indigenous totem pole as the background, it brings a mysterious sense of early civilization into the image. The main subject is an ancient bronze horse inspired by China's Sanxingdui style. Using oil pastels, the young artist creates bold, powerful lines and color blocks that suggest the weight, texture, and historical feeling of bronze. The Indigenous totem and ancient Shu civilization echo each other in the same composition, creating an imaginative dialogue between cultures. The work reflects the child's curiosity about ancient civilizations and celebrates the diversity of human culture and artistic imagination.
                    </div>
                    <h3><b>Comments</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
- Strong and imaginative concept, combining the two cultures<br>
- Effective use of bold lines and oil pastel<br> 
- Good composition and balance of images<br>
- Expresses curiosity, creativity, and respect for cultural diversity<br>
- Demonstrates strong potential for artistic growth
                    </div>           
