					  <h2><b>Partnership Details</b></h2>
					  <div class="text-muted checked-list" style="font-size: 18px; margin-top: 20px;">
1. Promotion and organization. Each school or organization will help promote the event through posters and posts, and encourage students to register and submit works.<br/>
2. Artwork collection. Each school or organization will collect and register artworks using the unified form and collect registration fees on behalf of the committee.<br/>
3. Submission. After artworks are collected and registration is complete, schools will verify student numbers provided by the organizing committee and confirm that participant information is complete and accurate before submitting works according to the unified schedule. Artists will also photograph and upload all works to the competition website.<br/>
4. Judging will include preliminary and final rounds.<br/>
Preliminary round: first, online preliminary judging will select the top 50% of works based on scores. Second, a preliminary judging panel, formed by drawing five professional teachers from partner organizations, will select an additional 10% from the remaining works. After the preliminary round, 60% of the works will proceed to final judging by three well-known local artists, who will select first, second, third, excellence, and rising star awards, with an overall award rate of 50%. All participants will receive a participation certificate.<br/>
5. Awards Ceremony: schools are asked to organize students to attend the ceremony and visit the exhibition on site. The ceremony is also a platform for teachers and students from Ottawa art schools to meet, exchange, and learn from one another.<br/>
6. Partner recognition: partner organizations will be acknowledged in posts, on the website, in video promotion, and during the awards ceremony.
