                    <h3><b>1. Express Yourself: “Art is the breath of the soul” - Picasso</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
Picasso once said, “Every child is born an artist. The problem is how to remain an artist once we grow up.” The Year of the Horse painting competition is a chance to rediscover that original spark, show childlike wonder, and express yourself. Through painting, let the vitality in your heart bloom on paper and let the creative process become a cleansing experience for the spirit.
                        </div>
                    </div>        
                </div>  
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>2. Release Imagination and Connect with Van Gogh</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
Van Gogh once said, “I dream my painting and then I paint my dream.” This is a boundless journey of imagination. With an open theme and free creativity, you can paint the Year of the Horse as you see it in your heart. Let your work shine as uniquely as Van Gogh's starry sky, turning your inner wonders into reality like a dream.
                        </div>
                    </div>        
                </div>        
            </div>  
            <div class="row" style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">              
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>3. Show Your Talent: “Life is the source of art” - Leonardo da Vinci</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
Leonardo da Vinci reminds us that we can observe the natural world and draw inspiration from it. In the Year of the Horse, a year symbolizing wisdom and vitality, use your observations of life to interpret the horse year through your brush. Turn your blessings and hopes for the new year into an artwork and let your talent shine on this stage.
                        </div>
                    </div>        
                </div>  
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>4. Build Skills and Share with Fellow Art Lovers</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
Cezanne said that great art is always shared with others. Joining the competition is not only a process of self-expression, but also an opportunity to communicate with teachers and friends and grow together. Share ideas, exchange techniques, and experience a sense of achievement with other students who love art, celebrating a Year of the Horse filled with artistic energy.
                        </div>
                    </div>        
                </div>        
            </div> 
            <div class="row" style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;">              
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <h3><b>5. Let Your Artwork Carry Blessings, in Tribute to W. B. Yeats</b></h3>
                    <div class="text-muted">
						<div class="text-muted" style="font-size: 18px;">
Yeats reminds us not only to plant beautiful seeds in the heart, but to let them bloom. Let your artwork become a warm blessing, sharing your wishes through colorful images. No matter the size of the work, it can become part of the beauty people share in the new year. Let your painting travel outward like a blessing, carrying warmth with it.
                        </div>
                    </div>        
                </div>  
